        <body><div type="bibliography">
                
                <p><bibl><ptr target="#jmr2012"/>, n. <citedRange>A.11</citedRange> (no image)</bibl>, whence
                    <bibl><ptr target="#SEG"/>, <citedRange>62.1795.5</citedRange></bibl>;
                    <bibl><ptr target="#IGCyr"/> <citedRange>116700</citedRange></bibl>.</p>
            </div><div type="edition" xml:lang="grc" xml:space="preserve">
                
                <ab>
                    <lb n="1"/><persName type="attested"><name><gap reason="lost" extent="unknown" unit="character"/></name></persName> 
                    <persName type="divine" ref="#Demeter"><name nymRef="#Δημήτηρ"><supplied reason="lost">Δημητρὶ</supplied></name></persName> 
                    καὶ <persName type="divine" ref="#Kore"><name nymRef="#Κόρη">Κόρη<supplied reason="lost">ι</supplied></name></persName>
	 </ab>
            </div><div type="apparatus" xml:space="preserve">
            
                <p/>
 </div><div type="translation" xml:space="preserve" xml:lang="fr">
            <p><supplied reason="lost">Untel</supplied> <supplied reason="subaudible">a consacré ce monument</supplied> à <supplied reason="lost">Dèmèter</supplied>
            et Korè.</p>
         </div><div type="translation" xml:space="preserve" xml:lang="en">
            <p><supplied reason="lost">So-and-so</supplied> <supplied reason="subaudible">dedicated this monument</supplied> to <supplied reason="lost">Demeter</supplied>
            and Kore.</p>
         </div><div type="translation" xml:space="preserve" xml:lang="it">
            <p><supplied reason="lost">Il tale</supplied> <supplied reason="subaudible">ha dedicato questo monumento</supplied> a <supplied reason="lost">Demetra</supplied>
            e Kore.</p>
         </div><div type="commentary">
                
                <p>There should have stood at left at least the name of the dedicator, either on the very base if it was wide enough or on an adjacent block.</p>
	<p/>
            </div></body>
